org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.client.alpha

Interface IMqttDeliveryToken<C>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - The OSGI Promise
    All Superinterfaces:
    IMqttToken<IMqttDeliveryResult<C>,C>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MqttDeliveryToken

    public interface IMqttDeliveryToken<C>
extends IMqttToken<IMqttDeliveryResult<C>,C>
    Provides a mechanism for tracking the delivery of a message.

    A subclass of IMqttToken that allows the delivery of a message to be tracked. Unlike instances of IMqttToken delivery tokens can be used across connection and client restarts. This enables the delivery of a messages to be tracked after failures.

    A list of delivery tokens for in-flight messages can be obtained using IMqttCommonClient.getPendingDeliveryTokens(). A getPromise().getValue() call can then be used to block until the delivery is complete.

    An action is in progress until getPromise().isDone() returns true. If a client shuts down before delivery is complete an exception is returned. As long as the Java Runtime is not stopped a delivery token is valid across a connection disconnect and reconnect. In the event the client is shut down the getPendingDeliveryTokens method can be used once the client is restarted to obtain a list of delivery tokens for inflight messages.

        IMqttMessage getMessage()
                 throws org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.MqttException
        Returns the message associated with this token.

        Until the message has been delivered, the message being delivered will be returned. Once the message has been delivered null will be returned.

        Returns:
        the message associated with this token or null if already delivered.
        Throws:
